{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875814872,"sessionID":"ses_2858f6106ffeAtBNfTYMwiEaoo","part":{"id":"prt_d7a71c382001Ms4zumLJK0wWUI","messageID":"msg_d7a71b4b0001h46LBecHKOTZBA","sessionID":"ses_2858f6106ffeAtBNfTYMwiEaoo","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_b9220d3f2bcb447698c4b47a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-033\n- **Module**: root\n- **Language**: Makefile\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe Makefile serves as the central build orchestration layer for the AgentCube project, providing a unified CLI interface for all development, build, test, and deployment operations. It bridges Go source compilation, Docker image building, testing workflows, and development environment management under a consistent `make` interface.\n\n### 1.2 Target Hierarchy\n\n```\nMakefile\n├── Configuration Variables\n│   ├── DOCKER_REGISTRY, DOCKER_TAG, GO_VERSION, BINARY_VERSION\n│   └── BINARIES, GO_LDFLAGS, BUILD_FLAGS\n│\n├── Binary Build Targets (Primary)\n│   ├── build              # Default: build all binaries\n│   ├── build-router\n│   ├── build-workload-manager\n│   ├── build-agentd\n│   └── build-picod\n│\n├── Cross-Compilation Targets\n│   ├── cross-build        # All platforms\n│   ├── build-linux-amd64\n│   ├── build-linux-arm64\n│   ├── build-darwin-amd64\n│   └── build-darwin-arm64\n│\n├── Docker Build Targets (AR-032)\n│   ├── docker-build\n│   ├── docker-build-router\n│   ├── docker-build-workload-manager\n│   ├── docker-build-agentd\n│   ├── docker-push\n│   └── validate-dockerfiles\n│\n├── Test Targets\n│   ├── test              # Default: test-unit\n│   ├── test-unit\n│   └── test-cover\n│\n├── Code Quality Targets\n│   ├── lint\n│   ├── lint-fix\n│   └── fmt\n│\n├── Development Targets\n│   ├── dev               # Default: dev-docker\n│   └── dev-docker\n│\n├── Cleanup Targets\n│   ├── clean\n│   └── docker-clean\n│\n└── Utility Targets\n    ├── help\n    ├── version\n    └── deps\n```\n\n### 1.3 Component Responsibilities\n\n| Component | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------------|\n| Binary Build | Compiles Go source to platform-specific executables |\n| Cross-Compile | Generates binaries for multiple OS/architecture combinations |\n| Docker Build | Invokes Docker build with multi-stage builds for minimal images |\n| Test | Executes unit tests with coverage reporting |\n| Lint/Format | Enforces code quality standards |\n| Development | Starts local development environment |\n| Utilities | Provides help, version info, dependency checking |\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Configuration Variables\n\n```makefile\n# Registry and versioning\nDOCKER_REGISTRY ?= agentcube\nDOCKER_TAG      ?= latest\nGO_VERSION      ?= 1.24\nBINARY_VERSION  ?= dev\n\n# Binary configuration\nBINARIES := router workload-manager agentd picod\nGO_LDFLAGS := -s -w -X main.version=$(BINARY_VERSION)\n\n# Build configuration\nCGO_ENABLED := 0\nGOOS_DEFAULT := linux\nGOARCH_DEFAULT := amd64\nBUILD_DIR := bin\n\n# Test configuration\nTEST_FLAGS := -v -short\nCOVERAGE_PROFILE := coverage.out\nCOVERAGE_REPORT := coverage.html\n```\n\n### 2.2 Target Categories\n\n| Category | Type | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| Binary targets | File-based | Produce binary executables in `bin/` |\n| Docker targets | Image-based | Produce Docker images |\n| Test targets | Process-based | Run test suites |\n| Utility targets | Informational | Display help/version |\n\n### 2.3 Output Directory Structure\n\n```\nbin/\n├── router              # Linux amd64 (default)\n├── workload-manager\n├── agentd\n├── picod\n├── linux-amd64/\n│   ├── router\n│   ├── workload-manager\n│   ├── agentd\n│   └── picod\n├── linux-arm64/\n├── darwin-amd64/\n└── darwin-arm64/\n```\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Binary Build API\n\n#### `make build`\n\n- **Description**: Build all binaries for the current platform\n- **Parameters**: None (uses defaults)\n- **Output**: Creates `bin/{router,workload-manager,agentd,picod}`\n- **Flags**: `CGO_ENABLED=0`, ldflags with version injection\n- **Exit Code**: 0 on success, non-zero on failure\n\n#### `make build-<binary>`\n\n- **Description**: Build a specific binary\n- **Valid Targets**: `router`, `workload-manager`, `agentd`, `picod`\n- **Output**: Creates `bin/<binary>`\n- **Example**: `make build-router` → `bin/router`\n\n### 3.2 Cross-Compilation API\n\n#### `make cross-build`\n\n- **Description**: Build for all supported platforms\n- **Output**: Creates `bin/{linux,darwin}-{amd64,arm64}/*`\n- **Targets**:\n  - `make build-linux-amd64` → `bin/linux-amd64/`\n  - `make build-linux-arm64` → `bin/linux-arm64/`\n  - `make build-darwin-amd64` → `bin/darwin-amd64/`\n  - `make build-darwin-arm64` → `bin/darwin-arm64/`\n\n### 3.3 Docker Build API\n\n#### `make docker-build`\n\n- **Description**: Build all Docker images\n- **Output**: Images tagged as `{DOCKER_REGISTRY}-{component}:{DOCKER_TAG}` and `:latest`\n- **Dependencies**: Requires Docker daemon running\n\n#### `make docker-build-<component>`\n\n- **Valid Components**: `router`, `workload-manager`, `agentd`\n- **Output**: Single image built and tagged\n\n### 3.4 Test API\n\n#### `make test`\n\n- **Description**: Run unit tests (default target)\n- **Flags**: `-v -short`\n- **Output**: Test results to stdout\n\n#### `make test-unit`\n\n- **Description**: Run only unit tests\n- **Flags**: `-v ./...`\n\n#### `make test-cover`\n\n- **Description**: Run tests with coverage\n- **Output**:\n  - `coverage.out` (raw profile)\n  - `coverage.html` (HTML report)\n  - Coverage percentage to stdout\n\n### 3.5 Code Quality API\n\n#### `make lint`\n\n- **Description**: Run golangci-lint\n- **Flags**: `./...` (all packages)\n- **Exit Code**: Non-zero if lint errors found\n\n#### `make lint-fix`\n\n- **Description**: Run linter with auto-fix\n- **Flags**: `--fix`\n\n#### `make fmt`\n\n- **Description**: Format code\n- **Tools**: `gofmt -w -s`, `goimports -w`\n\n### 3.6 Development API\n\n#### `make dev`\n\n- **Description**: Start development environment\n- **Default**: Invokes `dev-docker`\n\n#### `make dev-docker`\n\n- **Description**: Start services via docker-compose\n- **Command**: `docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d`\n\n### 3.7 Utility API\n\n#### `make help`\n\n- **Description**: Display all available targets\n- **Format**: Categorized help text\n\n#### `make version`\n\n- **Description**: Display current build version\n- **Output**: `BINARY_VERSION` value\n\n#### `make deps`\n\n- **Description**: Verify required dependencies\n- **Checks**: Go, Docker, (optional) golangci-lint\n\n### 3.8 Configuration Override API\n\n| Variable | Override Syntax | Default |\n|----------|----------------|---------|\n| Registry | `make DOCKER_REGISTRY=custom build` | `agentcube` |\n| Tag | `make DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0 build` | `latest` |\n| Version | `make BINARY_VERSION=1.0.0 build` | `dev` |\n| Go Version | `make GO_VERSION=1.23 docker-build` | `1.24` |\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Dependency Errors\n\n#### Missing Go Installation\n\n```\nError: Go is required but not installed.\nPlease install Go 1.24+: https://go.dev/dl/\n```\n\n**Mitigation**: `make deps` checks Go availability before build targets.\n\n#### Missing Docker\n\n```\nError: Docker is required but not installed.\nPlease install Docker: https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/\n```\n\n**Mitigation**: `make deps` checks Docker availability.\n\n#### Missing Source Code\n\n```\ngo build: cannot load package: package ./cmd/router not found\n```\n\n**Behavior**: Go's native error messages are propagated directly.\n\n### 4.2 Build Failures\n\n| Scenario | Behavior | Exit Code |\n|----------|----------|-----------|\n| Binary compilation fails | Propagate go build error | Non-zero |\n| Docker build fails | Propagate docker error | Non-zero |\n| Test failure | Show test output | Non-zero |\n| Lint errors | Show lint report | Non-zero |\n\n### 4.3 Cleanup Errors\n\n```makefile\ndocker-clean:\n\tdocker rmi $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-router:$(DOCKER_TAG) ... 2>/dev/null || true\n```\n\n**Behavior**: Silently ignore missing images (using `|| true`).\n\n### 4.4 Validation Errors\n\n```makefile\nvalidate-dockerfiles:\n\tdocker build -f docker/base.Dockerfile --target builder --no-run . || \\\n\t\t(echo \"base.Dockerfile validation failed\" && exit 1)\n```\n\n**Behavior**: Explicit error messages with context.\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Testing Targets\n\n| Target | Purpose | Verification |\n|--------|---------|--------------|\n| `make test` | Default test suite | All tests pass |\n| `make test-unit` | Unit tests only | `-short` flag skips integration |\n| `make test-cover` | Coverage analysis | Coverage ≥ 70% target |\n\n### 5.2 Integration Testing\n\n```makefile\ntest-integration:\n\tgo test -v -tags=integration ./integration/...\n```\n\n**Requirement**: Tag-based test isolation (`-tags=integration`).\n\n### 5.3 Makefile Target Testing\n\n| Scenario ID | Test Case | Verification Method |\n|------------|-----------|---------------------|\n| MAKE-001 | `make build` | Verify `bin/` contains all 4 binaries |\n| MAKE-002 | `make build-router` | Verify only `bin/router` exists |\n| MAKE-003 | `make cross-build` | Verify all 4 platform directories exist |\n| MAKE-004 | `make test` | Verify test output shows pass/fail |\n| MAKE-005 | `make lint` | Verify lint exits non-zero on errors |\n| MAKE-006 | `make fmt` | Verify code formatting applied |\n| MAKE-007 | `make help` | Verify help text displays |\n| MAKE-008 | `make clean` | Verify `bin/` removed |\n\n### 5.4 Acceptance Criteria Mapping\n\n| Delta Spec ID | Acceptance Criteria | Test Method |\n|----------------|---------------------|-------------|\n| AR-033-001 | `make build` produces binaries | File existence check |\n| AR-033-010 | `make cross-build` all platforms | Directory structure check |\n| AR-033-011 | `make docker-build` | Image existence check |\n| AR-033-016 | `make test` | Test exit code |\n| AR-033-018 | `make test-cover` | Coverage file exists |\n| AR-033-019 | `make lint` | Non-zero on errors |\n| AR-033-026 | `make help` | Output contains target names |\n| AR-033-034 | Missing Go error | Error message check |\n\n## 6. Implementation Notes\n\n### 6.1 PHONY Targets\n\nAll non-file targets declared as `.PHONY`:\n\n```makefile\n.PHONY: build build-router build-workload-manager build-agentd build-picod\n.PHONY: cross-build build-linux-amd64 build-linux-arm64 build-darwin-amd64 build-darwin-arm64\n.PHONY: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-workload-manager docker-build-agentd\n.PHONY: test test-unit test-integration test-cover\n.PHONY: lint lint-fix fmt\n.PHONY: dev dev-docker\n.PHONY: clean docker-clean\n.PHONY: help version deps\n```\n\n### 6.2 Platform Independence\n\n- Avoid shell-specific commands (`$(shell ...)` minimal usage)\n- Use Go's cross-platform compilation (`GOOS`, `GOARCH`)\n- Path separators: Use `/` (Make handles Windows conversion)\n\n### 6.3 Self-Documenting\n\nHelp target provides categorized output:\n\n```\nAgentCube Makefile Targets\n\nBuild:\n  make build              Build all binaries for current platform\n  make build-<binary>     Build specific binary (router|workload-manager|agentd|picod)\n  make cross-build        Build for all platforms\n\nDocker:\n  make docker-build       Build all Docker images\n  make docker-push        Push images to registry\n...\n```\n\n## 7. Relationship to Other ARs\n\n| AR | Relationship |\n|----|--------------|\n| AR-032 | Docker multi-stage builds use this Makefile for binary compilation |\n| AR-030 | Helm chart deployment independent |\n| CI/CD Pipeline | Consumes `make build`, `make test`, `make docker-build` |\n\n## 8. References\n\n- Proposal: `changes/AR-033/proposal.md`\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md`\n- Existing Makefile: `Makefile`\n- Go Cross-Compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n- golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/design.md","time":{"start":1775875814858,"end":1775875814869}}}}
